Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Bring a #large saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil. Peel and chop the @baking potato{1} into 2cm chunks.

When boiling, add the potato to the water and cook until you can easily slip a #knife{} through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @onion{1} into small pieces.

Heat the @butter{30%g} in a #large frying pan{} on medium heat.

Once melted, add the onion, season with @salt{pinch} and @ground black pepper{} and fry, stirring occasionally, until golden and softened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

While the onion fries, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{70%g}.

Put the @plain naans{2} onto a #large baking tray{}. Sprinkle with a little water, then scatter over the cheese. Pop them onto the middle shelf of your oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}.

In a #large bowl{}, combine the @cider vinegar{15%ml}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with @salt{pinch} and @ground black pepper{} and set aside.

Add the @sugar{1%tsp} for the onions to the onion pan and cook until caramelised, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the garlic, @curry powder mix{2%sachets}, @white cumin seeds{1%sachet} and fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute} more.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{}.

Add the potatoes to the onions, then use a #spoon{} to lightly mash the potatoes and stir to coat in the butter and spices. Stir in the @mango chutney{40%g} and season with @salt{pinch} and @ground black pepper{}.

Load the potato mixture onto one half of each warmed naan. Press the potato down with the back of a spoon to lightly bind it to the naan.

Carefully fold the other half of the naan over. Press down firmly to sandwich the naans together.

Give the #frying pan{} a quick wipe, then heat a drizzle of @olive oil{for frying} in the (now empty) frying pan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the folded naans, pressing down with a #spatula{} or a #heavy-bottomed pan{}.

Cook, pressing frequently, until the naan is golden and toasted, ~{2-4%minutes} on each side.

Just before serving, add the baby plum tomatoes and @baby leaf mix{50%g} to the dressing and toss to coat.

Share the stuffed naans between your plates. Add the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} on the side for dipping.

Serve the tomato and baby leaf salad alongside. Enjoy!